Wash and dry produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and thinly
slice @cremini mushrooms{4%ounce} (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a #small pot{} over medium-high heat (medium
pot for 4 servings). Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened,
~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4); bring to a
boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender,
~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{}, preferably #nonstick
{}, over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, a pinch of
@salt{} and @pepper{}, and as many @?chili flakes{1%teaspoon} as you like. Cook,
stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and mushrooms are slightly
crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @sesame seeds{1%tablespoon} and cook, stirring, until lightly golden and
fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out
pan.

Pat @chicken breast{10%ounce}(chopped) dry with #paper towels{}; season with a
large pinch of salt and pepper.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in #pan{} used for veggies over medium-high heat.
Add chicken in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and
cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a #small bowl{}, whisk together @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon},
@sriracha{1%teaspoon}, half the @cornstarch{1%tablespoon}, and 1/3 cup water (all
the cornstarch and 2/3 cup water for 4 servings).

Once chicken is done cooking, reduce heat to low and add sauce mixture. Cook,
stirring, until sauce has thickened and chicken is well coated, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} (2 TBSP for 4).

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; gently stir in veggies and 1/4 tsp @sesame oil{1%tablespoon}
(½ tsp for 4 servings). (Be sure to measure sesame oil—we sent more!) Taste and
season with salt if desired.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with chicken and any sauce from pan. Garnish
with scallion greens and serve.